{"type":"message","id":"0ab6722d","parentId":"bdfbcf5e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:17:41.731Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_mj72rkoizr2w_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5271\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='' file='' new_len=0\n[mutation parse failed] old='' file='' new_len=0\n[master f17772f] pulse: 2026-03-24 131715\n 5 files changed, 223 insertions(+), 124 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 131715.md\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 131615.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 131715 - The CFI Compression Experiment revealed that pure CFI thresholds fail due to \"constant format\" tokens (freq�160, CFI=1.00) that are metaprogramming artifacts with zero information content. The next step identified is Strategy C: hybrid CFIxFreq scoring.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"good-ocean","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5271\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='' file='' new_len=0\n[mutation parse failed] old='' file='' new_len=0\n[master f17772f] pulse: 2026-03-24 131715\n 5 files changed, 223 insertions(+), 124 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 131715.md\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 131615.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 131715 - The CFI Compression Experiment revealed that pure CFI thresholds fail due to \"constant format\" tokens (freq�160, CFI=1.00) that are metaprogramming artifacts with zero information content. The next step identified is Strategy C: hybrid CFIxFreq scoring.\n","name":"powershell Bypass"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774372661728}}
{"type":"message","id":"77f54525","parentId":"0ab6722d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:17:41.735Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_mj72rkoizr2w_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 131615\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action would best advance the goals.\r\n\r\nKey pending items:\r\n1. Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n2. Distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n3. Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Design actual compression network\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step would be to implement the hybrid scoring function that combines CFI and frequency, as this directly addresses the constant format problem and moves toward the compression objective.\r\n\r\nFrom the notes:\r\n- Three-dimensional compression filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n- Compression objective: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nI should implement this scoring function in a script that can process the pulse data and generate scores. This would be a concrete file edit that advances the hybrid scoring experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script that implements this scoring and can be run against the existing pulse data to validate the approach.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe hybrid CFI×Freq scoring formula is well-specified: `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)`. This needs implementation to validate it distinguishes constant-format tokens (score inflated by high freq) from research trajectory tokens (balanced CFI×freq signal).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a Python scoring script that implements the hybrid formula against existing pulse token data, producing ranked token scores to validate the approach before running the full experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nHybrid CFI×Freq Token Scorer\r\nImplements: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nPurpose: Distinguish constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \r\n         research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5)\r\n\"\"\"\r\nimport json\r\nimport math\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\ndef score_token(cfi: float, freq: int) -> float:\r\n    \"\"\"Hybrid scoring: CFI × normalized frequency.\"\"\"\r\n    freq_component = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\r\n    return cfi * freq_component\r\n\r\ndef analyze_pulses(pulse_dir: Path = Path(\"pulse_logs\")):\r\n    \"\"\"Analyze tokens from pulse logs with hybrid scoring.\"\"\"\r\n    # Load all pulse token data\r\n    token_data = {}  # token -> {\"cfi\": float, \"freq\": int}\r\n    \r\n    for pulse_file in sorted(pulse_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.json\")):\r\n        try:\r\n            with open(pulse_file) as f:\r\n                data = json.load(f)\r\n                for token_info in data.get(\"tokens\", []):\r\n                    token = token_info[\"token\"]\r\n                    cfi = token_info.get(\"cfi\", 0.0)\r\n                    if token not in token_data:\r\n                        token_data[token] = {\"cfi\": cfi, \"freq\": 0}\r\n                    token_data[token][\"freq\"] += 1\r\n                    # CFI is per-pulse, use max for cross-pulse\r\n                    token_data[token][\"cfi\"] = max(token_data[token][\"cfi\"], cfi)\r\n        except (json.JSONDecodeError, FileNotFoundError):\r\n            continue\r\n    \r\n    # Score all tokens\r\n    scored = []\r\n    for token, data in token_data.items():\r\n        s = score_token(data[\"cfi\"], data[\"freq\"])\r\n        scored.append({\r\n            \"token\": token,\r\n            \"score\": s,\r\n            \"cfi\": data[\"cfi\"],\r\n            \"freq\": data[\"freq\"]\r\n        })\r\n    \r\n    # Sort by score descending\r\n    scored.sort(key=lambda x: x[\"score\"], reverse=True)\r\n    \r\n    # Report results\r\n    print(\"=\" * 70)\r\n    print(\"HYBRID CFI×FREQ SCORING RESULTS\")\r\n    print(\"=\" * 70)\r\n    print(f\"\\nTotal tokens analyzed: {len(scored)}\")\r\n    \r\n    print(\"\\n--- TOP 20 TOKENS (High score = research signal) ---\")\r\n    for i, item in enumerate(scored[:20], 1):\r\n        print(f\"{i:3}. score={item['score']:.3f} cfi={item['cfi']:.2f} freq={item['freq']:3d}  '{item['token']}'\")\r\n    \r\n    print(\"\\n--- BOTTOM 20 TOKENS (Low score = constant format/metadata) ---\")\r\n    for i, item in enumerate(scored[-20:], len(scored)-19):\r\n        print(f\"{i:3}. score={item['score']:.3f} cfi={item['cfi']:.2f} freq={item['freq']:3d}  '{item['token']}'\")\r\n    \r\n    print(\"\\n--- CONSTANT FORMAT TOKENS (cfi=1.0, freq>100) ---\")\r\n    constant = [x for x in scored if x['cfi'] == 1.0 and x['freq'] > 100]\r\n    for item in constant[:10]:\r\n        print(f\"  score={item['score']:.3f} cfi={item['cfi']:.2f} freq={item['freq']:3d}  '{item['token']}'\")\r\n    \r\n    # Save full results\r\n    output_path = Path(\"research/cfi_freq_scores.json\")\r\n    with open(output_path, 'w') as f:\r\n        json.dump(scored, f, indent=2)\r\n    print(f\"\\nFull results saved to: {output_path}\")\r\n    \r\n    return scored\r\n\r\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\r\n    analyze\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 13:16:33\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774372661731}}
